a-Path Carry-Conditioned Linearization Scaling

N=4: 3 variable bits / 56 total. 4 patterns. 42/49 all-zero. Entropy=2.0
N=6: 17 variable bits / 84 total. 33 patterns. 0/50 all-zero. Entropy=5.0

Scaling is sub-ideal: variable bits grow from 3 to 17 (roughly N^2/3).
At N=8: expect ~40-60 variable a-path bits. At N=32: estimate 200+.
The a-path linearization is costless at N=4 but grows for larger N.

However, the NUMBER OF VALID PATTERNS grows much slower than 2^(var bits):
  N=4: 4 patterns out of 2^3 = 8 (50% hit rate)
  N=6: 33 patterns out of 2^17 = 131072 (0.025% hit rate)

The patterns are highly structured — not random subsets of carry space.
